</taxonomicName>
can be separated from 
<emphasis id="B915EAD1FF83FF80801CFE38C236FE35" box="[845,1026,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="153">
<taxonomicName id="4C614D40FF83FF80801CFE38C5CAFE35" authorityName="Busanello &amp; Irmler &amp; Caron" authorityYear="2020" box="[845,1022,441,467]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudastenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ribeirocostae">P. ribeirocostae</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
that has also reduced hind wings and short eyes, by the lighter coloration and even shorter eyes. The apical sclerites of aedeagus are more slender than those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C614D40FF83FF8083A9FD80C793FDFD" authorityName="Busanello &amp; Irmler &amp; Caron" authorityYear="2020" box="[248,423,513,539]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudastenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ribeirocostae">
