<subSubSection id="C37B6548FF83FF808396FDA7C549FBF2" pageId="14" pageNumber="153" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BDE36C3FF83FF808396FDA7C549FBF2" blockId="14.[151,1437,261,1188]" pageId="14" pageNumber="153">
<emphasis id="B915EAD1FF83FF808396FDA7C76DFDA6" bold="true" box="[199,345,549,576]" pageId="14" pageNumber="153">Description.</emphasis>
Body length: 
<quantity id="4C999B26FF83FF8082A6FDA7C46AFDA6" box="[503,606,549,576]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.31" pageId="14" pageNumber="153" unit="mm" value="3.31">3.31 mm</quantity>
. Coloration: head and elytra light brown; pronotum slightly lighter brown, nearly yellow; abdomen darker brown; first segment colored as elytra; following segments darker; darkened posteriad; legs and antennae yellow. Head 
<quantity id="4C999B26FF83FF808163FDEFC4A1FD6E" box="[562,661,621,648]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="14" pageNumber="153" unit="mm" value="0.45">0.45 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="4C999B26FF83FF808189FDEFC50FFD6E" box="[728,827,621,648]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" pageId="14" pageNumber="153" unit="mm" value="0.46">0.46 mm</quantity>
wide; widest close to posterior angles; posterior angles nearly rectangular; eyes small, only 0,2 times as long as total length of head and 0.4 times as long as postocular length; posterior central edge with inconspicuous depression in front of neck, with dense microtuberculate punctation and loose pubescence laterally. Pronotum 
<quantity id="4C999B26FF83FF8081F2FD5BC53CFD12" box="[675,776,729,756]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="14" pageNumber="153" unit="mm" value="0.45">0.45 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="4C999B26FF83FF80801EFD5BC580FD12" box="[847,948,729,756]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="14" pageNumber="153" unit="mm" value="0.45">0.45 mm</quantity>
wide; widest close to anterior angles; anterior margin slightly curved to obtuse anterior angles; sides conspicuously convergent to posterior angles; posterior margin straight; posterior margin only 0.70 times as wide as maximum width. Elytra 
<quantity id="4C999B26FF83FF80871AFCA3C29BFCDA" box="[1099,1199,801,828]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="14" pageNumber="153" unit="mm" value="0.42">0.42 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="4C999B26FF83FF8087A5FCA3C36CFCDA" box="[1268,1368,801,828]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="153" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.30 mm</quantity>
wide; widest close to posterior angles; sides convergent to humeral angles; humeral angles obtuse and inconspicuous; hind wings reduced; posterior margin semi-circular with incision at suture; suture 0.8 times as long as total length; punctures slightly larger than on head and pronotum and pubescence longer; posterior margin with fringe of short dark setae. Abdomen with less deep microtuberculate punctation than fore-body but with longer pubescence pointing posteriad. Aedeagus 
<quantity id="4C999B26FF83FF8082F8FC57C438FC16" box="[425,524,981,1008]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.9" pageId="14" pageNumber="153" unit="mm" value="0.49">0.49 mm</quantity>
long; subparallel; 3.76 times as long as wide; slightly constricted in front of apex; sclerites 
<quantity id="4C999B26FF83FF8083ABFC7BC76AFBF2" box="[250,350,1017,1044]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="153" unit="mm" value="0.05">0.05 mm</quantity>
long; acute at apex and without hooks (
<figureCitation id="135A2A46FF83FF80804DFC7BC545FBF2" box="[796,881,1017,1044]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–54" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1895,1920]" captionTargetBox="[232,1346,220,1805]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[164,1424,181,1869]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 48–54. Aedeagus of Pseudastenus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively, figures 51–54 including microscopic detail of basal slerites. 48. P. ribeirocostae sp. nov.; 49. P. ferrugineus sp. nov.; 50. P. latus sp. nov.; 51. P. barretoi; 52. P. oculatus sp. nov.; 53. P. amazonicus sp. nov.; 54. P. schubarti sp. nov. Scale bar: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3724309" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3724309/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="153">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37B6548FF83FF808396FB9CC2B8FB45" pageId="14" pageNumber="153" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BDE36C3FF83FF808396FB9CC22EFBBD" blockId="14.[151,1437,261,1188]" pageId="14" pageNumber="153">
<emphasis id="B915EAD1FF83FF808396FB9CC77AFBDE" bold="true" box="[199,334,1054,1080]" pageId="14" pageNumber="153">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of the species honors Dr. Herbert Schubart, the former director of the INPA, Manaus, who assigned his staphylinid collection to my disposal in 1976 for further study.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDE36C3FF83FF808396FBE7C301FB66" blockId="14.[151,1437,261,1188]" box="[199,1333,1125,1152]" pageId="14" pageNumber="153">
<emphasis id="B915EAD1FF83FF808396FBE7C7FEFB66" bold="true" box="[199,458,1125,1152]" pageId="14" pageNumber="153">Geographical records</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C614D40FF83FF808289FBE4C469FB99" authorityName="Busanello &amp; Irmler &amp; Caron" authorityYear="2020" box="[472,605,1125,1151]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudastenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schubarti">
<emphasis id="B915EAD1FF83FF808289FBE4C469FB99" box="[472,605,1125,1151]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="153">P. schubarti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected in the region of the city of 
<collectingRegion id="49A5F821FF83FF80877FFBE7C2E4FB99" box="[1070,1232,1125,1151]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="14" pageNumber="153">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry id="F3767653FF83FF80878EFBE7C31DFB66" box="[1247,1321,1125,1152]" name="Brazil" pageId="14" pageNumber="153">Brazil</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDE36C3FF83FF808396FB0BC2B8FB45" blockId="14.[151,1437,261,1188]" box="[199,1164,1161,1188]" pageId="14" pageNumber="153">
<emphasis id="B915EAD1FF83FF808396FB0BC7BEFB42" bold="true" box="[199,394,1161,1188]" pageId="14" pageNumber="153">Biological notes.</emphasis>
No further information is available about the ecology of the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
